{"id": 57896, "date": "2025-08-03T04:00:55", "date_gmt": "2025-08-03T11:00:55", "guid": {"rendered": "https://estreetshuffle.com/?p=57896"}, "modified": "2026-06-18T04:41:34", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-18T11:41:34", "slug": "kingdom-of-days-august-3-2", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2025/08/03/kingdom-of-days-august-3-2/", "title": {"rendered": "August 3"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p><strong>1974:\u00a0</strong>Bruce and the E Street Band play their very last opening set ever, at the Wollman Ice Rink in New York City&#8217;s Central Park. The story will become legend: Bruce is a late substitution for original headliner Boz Scaggs, but managers for opening act Anne Murray successfully argue that she has a greater claim to the headliner slot than Bruce does due to her greater album sales. Murray therefore ends up headlining a show that was originally advertised with Bruce as the headliner, and as a result only a quarter of the crowd stays to the end of Murray&#8217;s set. Bruce has become an impossible act to follow, and no one will attempt it again.</p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"3434\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1974-0803/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/1974-0803.jpg?fit=1054%2C540&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1054,540\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1974-0803\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/1974-0803.jpg?fit=758%2C389&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-3434 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/1974-0803.jpg?resize=758%2C388&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/1974-0803.jpg?w=1054&amp;ssl=1 1054w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/1974-0803.jpg?resize=300%2C154&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/1974-0803.jpg?resize=768%2C393&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/1974-0803.jpg?resize=1024%2C525&amp;ssl=1 1024w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1976:\u00a0</strong>Bruce debuts an early version of &#8220;The Promise&#8221; on Night Three of six at the Monmouth Arts Center in Red Bank. The lyrics are different from the final version, most notably the chorus. Take a listen&#8211;it&#8217;s the only time this version will ever be performed.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ku_IeAijmzs?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>1977:\u00a0</strong>Bruce and the E Street Band work on &#8220;Racing in the Street&#8221; at Atlantic Studios in New York City.</p>\n<p><strong>1988:\u00a0</strong>The Tunnel of Love Tour wraps up with a final show at Camp Nou in Barcelona.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xPd7_f9dLgQ?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/sya6FmwnHyM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<div id=\"v-0ivPeKdV-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='568' src='https://videopress.com/embed/0ivPeKdV?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9thsullhy8k?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" 